This approach not only eliminates the need for users to log in to the web console, which can be a cumbersome process, but it also mitigates the risk of unauthorized access to sensitive data on the server. Currently, most files on the server have read access for all users, which can pose a security risk. By implementing a privacy classification process, users can ensure that their data is only accessible to authorized individuals, reducing the risk of data breaches and maintaining the confidentiality of their data.
